	•	Do you take insurance?
	•	I am a private-pay practice, and do not currently accept insurance. However, several clients seek reimbursement through “out-of-network” coverage. I encourage all clients to check with their benefits to see if services are eligible for reimbursement. If so, I am happy to provide you with a “super bill” which can be submitted to your insurance company for potential reimbursement.
	•	 What forms of payment do you accept?
	•	I use a platform called Simple Practice where you will be able to set up billing information through a client portal. At the time of the session, the credit/debit card on file will be charged unless alternative forms of payment have been previously agreed upon. Cash, check, Venmo, and PayPal are also accepted forms of payment.
	•	Do you work with couples or families?
	•	Because I have found that multiple therapy participants are best served in more intensive healing settings, I only work with couples in intensive settings such as 2-4 day intensives. I do offer family sessions in 90-120 minute blocks. 
	•	Where are you located?
	•	My physical office is located at 6065 Lake Forrest Drive NW, Suite 250, Sandy Springs, GA 30328 in a building that requires stairs to access my office on the second floor. Therefore, for those who have mobility issues, virtual sessions and home visits are available. 
	•	What is the next step if I have more questions or am unsure?
	•	You can schedule a free 15-minute consultation. Request a consult here.
